How to open a file:

	using open() returns a file object:
		f = open(filename, mode, encoding=None)

how to write text in a file:

	mode can be:
		w = write
		r = read
		r+ = wr
		a = appending
	
	using the with keyword to open files:
		
		- with open("filename", "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:-

	so using:
		f.write() will write to the file but the with keyword needs to be there

how to read the full content of a file:

	using the read() function by ommiting the size or by making size negative

		f.read() or f.read(-1)

how to read a file line by line:

	using a loop and a readline() function

		for line in f:
			print(line)

